@Mean Old Lady 

I don't understand why everyone is jumping all over this?  It didn't affect the puzzle at all.  It was only a comment in the discussion of the puzzle, not the puzzle itself.

Or am I missing something?

@Browncoat 

Apparently we're just a hateful lot nowdays.  Politics, religion, crosswords...we just can't get past this feeling that everyone is cheating us in some way or another.

I promise you that I'd never submit a puzzle to the NYT, even if I were able.  To work on something month after month just to be rewarded with a tiny payment and a huge amount of criticism over every tiny detail?  Not for me.

@Nancy 

Look up Plug (jewellry) (sic) in Wikipedia. I’m sure you’ve seen that sort of adornment before. (And if you’re like me, you probably wondered why someone would do that to themselves.)

I gather that plug earrings come in different width (gauges), since one needs to start with a relatively small disc/ring and stretch the earlobe out over time.
